    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">

                <!-- Begin heading
        ===================
        * Use class "heading-center" or "heading-right" to align heading.
        * Use class "heading-xs", "heading-sm", "heading-md", "heading-lg" or "heading-xlg" to shange heading size.
        * Use class "heading-hover" to enable heading hover effect.
        * Use class "heading-uppercase" to enable uppercase letters.
        -->
                <div class="heading heading-lg text-white heading-hover wow fadeIn" data-wow-delay="0.2s">
                    <span class="heading-title-ghost">Services</span>
                    <h2 class="heading-title">Services</h2>

                    <!-- Begin divider
    ===================
    * Use class "hr-width-1", "hr-width-2" -> up to "hr-width-10" to change divider width.
    * Use class "hr-1x", "hr-2x", "hr-3x", "hr-4x" or "hr-5x" to change divider size.
    * Use class "hr-dotted", "hr-dashed" or "hr-double" to change divider style.
    -->
                    <hr class="hr-width-3 hr-5x border-main">
                    <!-- End divider -->

                    <p class="heading-tescription lead text-gray-2">
                        We make software! Our one and only service is <b>developing software</b>. Our work starts from the very birth of a project till the end of the software lifecycle.
                    </p>
                    <br>

                    <div class="row">
                        <img src="~/Content/images/desktop-work.png" class="img-responsive" style="max-width:350px;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" />
                    </div>

                    <div id="modalServices" class="inline-popup mfp-hide">
                        <div class="inline-popup-inner">
                            <div class="inline-popup-image bg-image" style="background-image: url(/Content/images/sw-development-lifecycle.png); background-position: 0% 0%; background-size: 100%"></div>
                            <div class="row margin-top-40">
                                <div class="col-md-8 margin-bottom-20">
                                    <h2 class="no-margin-top">Services</h2>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        We make software! Our one and only service is <b>developing software</b>.
                                        Our work starts from the very birth of a project till the end of the software lifecycle.
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        The first step of a software is modeling a real-world problem into a robust and elegant architecture. This architecture is
                                        composed of flexible <b>building blocks</b> (classes) and a meaningful <b>data structure</b>.
                                    </p>
                                    <p style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:40px">
                                        <img src="~/Content/images/sw-developers-desktop.png" class="img-responsive" alt="Software developer's desk. Not necessarily that tidy though." title="Software developer's desk. Not necessarily that tidy though." style="max-width:500px;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" />
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        Upon a well estabished architecture, we create versatile algorithms that solve the real-world problems. Creating clever
                                        algorithms is necessary but not sufficient for a robust software.
                                        The software is a woven fabric, composed of code pieces. We strictly follow universally accepted code standards,
                                        yielding a code as simple as possible, re-usable, modular, and easily updatable.
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        We issue a 1 year <b>free maintainence service</b> at the end of our all projects. All our
                                        software is delivered as open source, so the clients are free to continue on their own.
                                        Though we offer a yearly maintainence service that costs 15% of the project cost.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-4 margin-bottom-20 padding-left-40">
                                    <h2 class="no-margin-top">SW Lifecycle</h2>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        A software program is in many ways like a living organism. It starts its life with a mere <b>idea</b>.
                                        This idea is transformed into an abstract model after requirements analysis.
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        At the <b>design</b> step, this abstract model is transformed into a software architecture and software models
                                        such as classes and database models. The implementation step transforms this model into a real software.
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        But this software is only at its infancy. It grows mature along the <b>testing</b> and <b>evolution</b> processes.
                                    </p>
                                    <p class="info-box-text text-gray">
                                        And in fact, as long as the software is alive, software development process never ends. The process goes on with
                                        additions, modifications, adaptations, optimizations i.e. the maintainence step.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div> <!-- /.row -->
                        </div> <!-- /.inline-popup-inner -->
                        <a class="inline-popup-close" href="#"><i class="fas fa-times"></i></a>
                    </div><!-- Popup content. Class "mfp-hide" is required to make dialog hidden -->
                </div>
                <!-- End heading -->

            </div> <!-- Left column -->
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <div class="info-box info-box-4 info-box-white wow fadeIn">
                            <span class="info-box-icon rounded-icon bg-main text-white"><i class="far fa-drafting-compass"></i></span>
                            <div class="info-box-info">
                                <h4 class="info-box-title">Designing the Architecture</h4>
                                <p class="info-box-text text-gray-2">
                                    The first step is modeling a real-world problem into a robust and elegant architecture.
                                </p>
                            </div>
